Package org.greencheek.processio.domain

Stores the domain model objects that represent: CurrentProcessIO : Used to store temporarily the current io that has been obtain for the current process ProcessIO : Used to store the previous IO that has been recorded for the process, and the latest IO that has been recorded for the process

See:
          Description

Class Summary
CurrentProcessIO Stores the current io that has been recorded for the given process.
ProcessIO Represents the amount of IO that a process has performed.
 

Package org.greencheek.processio.domain Description

Stores the domain model objects that represent:

  • CurrentProcessIO : Used to store temporarily the current io that has been obtain for the current process
  • ProcessIO : Used to store the previous IO that has been recorded for the process, and the latest IO that has been recorded for the process
